Recommended resolution:
    128x128x128 (nu=eta=10 Mm km/s)
Comments:
    The initial magnetic field distribution is derived from a magnetogram.
    On the lower boundary there is time-dependent forcing.
    Heat conduction is here uniform (iheatcond='K-const').
    This example uses SI units, a non-uniform mesh in the z direction,
References:
    Gudiksen, B. V., and Nordlund, Å.: 2005, ``An Ab Initio Approach
    to the Solar Coronal Heating Problem,'' Astrophys. J. 618, 1020-1030
